# Zeteo

A terminal-based AI assistant with observability log analysis capabilities.

## Overview

Zeteo is a command-line AI assistant that combines conversational AI with observability log analysis. It provides a responsive terminal user interface with support for multiple AI providers and log backends.

## Quick Start

```bash
# Install
cargo install zeteo

# Run
export OPENAI_API_KEY=your-key
zeteo
```

## Configuration

Set AI provider via environment variables:

| Provider     | Variables                                        |
|--------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| OpenAI       | `OPENAI_API_KEY`                                 |
| Google AI    | `GOOGLE_API_KEY`                                 |
| Azure        | `AZURE_OPENAI_*`                                 |
| Vertex       | `GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT`, `GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION`  |
| Ollama       | `OLLAMA_MODEL`, `OLLAMA_BASE_URL`                |

Configure log backends in `config.json`. See `config.example.json`.

